    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that makes sense. but i've seen some people argue that the UN is actually more important now than ever because without it, things would just be total anarchy. do historians generally see those criticisms of the UN as legitimate systemic failures, or are they just people being unrealistic about how hard global diplomacy actually is?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
