      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Historians generally view the argument for the UN's necessity as a pragmatic acceptance of the current geopolitical reality, rather than a true endorsement of its effectiveness. While the UN prevents total anarchy by providing a framework for dialogue, this framework is inherently weak against determined state actors. The criticism of systemic failure is legitimate because the organization is structurally incapable of enforcing peace against powerful, self-interested nations.",
      "source": "target",
